{"word":"κεράννυμι","slug":"κεράννυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰεράννυμι</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> complex] <b>mix,</b> of diluting wine <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> water <b><a href='B:730 18:6'>Rv 18:6</a>.</b> In a dramatic oxymoron: <el>πινεῖν <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐκ\">ἐκ</a> οἴνου ϰεϰερασμένου ἀϰράτου</el> drink wine mixed unmixed = wine served full strength (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄκρατος\">ἄκρατος</a></el>) <b><a href='B:730 14:10'>14:10</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:κέραμος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:κέρας\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}